&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Flygreen&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Looking for a career with purpose? Flygreen is a leading private jet charter brokerage, focused on delivering our clients a world-class service through our cutting-edge technology and deep expertise. Our dedication to excellence sets us apart in the industry. We ensure every client is paired with the perfect aircraft solution, providing a seamless and memorable experience. We&#39;re seeking passionate, driven individuals to join our team and help shape the future of private aviation. If you’re passionate about operations and aviation, Flygreen is where you belong.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are looking for a detail-oriented Flight Operations Coordinator to join our growing team. In this role, you will support day-to-day charter operations, ensure smooth communication between clients, brokers, and operators, and manage logistics for each flight from booking through post-flight follow-up.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate private jet flight logistics — including scheduling, permits, and ground handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver exceptional hospitality and fulfill each client&#39;s unique service needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor active flights to ensure on-time departures and arrivals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the main point of contact for operators throughout the trip lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and verify flight documents, confirmations, and invoices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the sales and brokerage team with quotes, trip sheets, and updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle urgent operational needs, including after-hours support when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records and reports for all charter trips.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in charter operations, aviation dispatch, or travel coordination is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and multitasking skills under time-sensitive conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills with high attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English; French is an asset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Google Workspace; experience with aviation software is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work flexible hours (some evenings/weekends as flights require).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary $50,000-$60,000.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to develop professionally within a growing company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive benefits package: medical, dental, vision, RRSP (generous employer match), PTO, gym membership, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to join a dynamic company with likeminded individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Culture:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are building a team of winners. We are hard-working and determined to succeed!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We offer a welcoming, fun, and enjoyable team to belong to.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have a passion for travel and aviation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We host seasonal events and spontaneous team outings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;* Please note this a full-time on-site position, in Montreal, Quebec, Canada&lt;/div&gt;
