&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be the main point of contact to your list of clients. Customer requests will come in at varying hours. Jet Charter Sales Executives must remain available on-demand;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate new business leads through business development strategies, ie. networking, telephone and email communication, marketing campaigns, and other sales channels;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage, negotiate and close customer inquiries for private jet charter use;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide exemplary customer service and ensure a smooth booking and travel experience for clients;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate all details of your customer’s charter flights, with the various parties involved;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with customers and suppliers; to deliver fast and reliable customer service to your clients;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of customer interactions, bookings, and sales data, and provide regular reports to management;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date on market trends, competition, and customer needs to inform sales strategies and offerings;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate clients on the benefits of our private jet charter services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
